OL,7,F"It supports recommendations to limit
OL,8,Fthe consumption of processed meat and
OL,9,Funprocessed red meat to reduce type 2
OL,10,Fdiabetes cases in the population."
OL,12,FThe NHS advises people eating more
OL,13,Fthan 90g of red meat such as beef,
OL,14,Flamb, mutton, pork, veal, venison and
OL,15,Fgoat, or processed meat such as
OL,16,Fsausages, bacon, ham, salami and
OL,17,Fcorned beef a day, to cut down to 70g
OL,18,For less.
