OL,7,FDr Duane Mellor, dietitian and
OL,8,Fspokesperson for British Dietetic
OL,9,FAssociation, who was not involved in
OL,10,Fthe study, said: "The overall message
OL,11,Fto moderate meat intake is in line
OL,12,Fwith national healthy eating
OL,13,Fguidelines and advice to reduce risk
OL,14,Fof developing type 2 diabetes, which
OL,15,Finclude eating a diet which is based
OL,16,Fon vegetables, fruit, nuts, seeds,
OL,17,Fbeans, peas and lentils along with
OL,18,Fsome wholegrain and moderate amounts
OL,19,Fof meat and dairy with limited amounts
OL,20,Fof added fat, salt and sugar."
